bio.experienceSummary:
Hello,
My name is Gabriela, I'm a nanny since 2018 and love to be with kids! 
I have experience with ages 0 to 13 and I used to work as an English teacher for toddlers. I always like to improve kid's skills and think about a nice environment for them to grow up. I like to do a lot of arts and craft, play and make a lot of activities. I can describe myself as a calm, caring, very responsible, dedicated, hardworking, open-minded and adaptive.
I can wait to meet your family!

As a dedicated caregiver with a decade of experience, I am deeply committed to supporting families and fostering a nurturing, educational environment for children. My background in early child development and training in first aid and CPR allows me to confidently manage a wide range of situations.

My patient, detail-oriented, creative, and friendly nature helps me connect effortlessly with children and create a positive, engaging atmosphere. I prioritize open communication with parents, ensuring they are regularly updated about their child's day and any concerns that arise.

I am adept at enforcing household rules and enjoy engaging children in diverse activities. With my extensive experience, I can comfortably care for up to five children of various age groups, from infants to preteens.

Additionally, I am happy to assist with tasks such as cooking, meal preparation, light housekeeping, and travel arrangements, making me a versatile and reliable addition to your family.

As a nurturing caregiver with 15 years of experience, I've developed a knack for understanding children's needs. While majoring in Education in college, I found navigating complexity and empathy with children comes naturally to me. Additionally, after volunteering as a camp counselor for a children's camp for years, I have been able to engage with various ages .

I am approachable, level-headed, loving, and understanding. These traits help me to be a dependable caregiver while parents are away. My main priority is creating a safe, fun environment for children and give parents a much needed sense of peace!

description.originalText: Imani is wonderful with the kids. Very patient and caring and I love that she speaks Korean with them! She’s a joy to have around

bio.experienceSummary: I have babysat on and off for the past several years throughout high school, college and medical school. I have watched boys and girls, ranging in age, from 18m to 13y. I am currently in my fourth and final year of medical school, with plans to start residency in the summer.

Hello parents, I'd describe my personality as professional, bubbly, and fun. 
I like working with kid because they're just careless and free. They do not think about getting their clothes dirty or listen to grown ups if that means their going into a new adventure. Caring, play, correct and listen to them it's also a way to shape them into lovely adults in the future 
I started working with kids back in my country, I was a teacher assistant for at least a year in a Daycare. After seeing they way I approached their kids and the way they looked out for me, parents starter reaching out about babysitting after school
In my spare time, I like to listen to podcast while working out. I love to bake, cookies, breads, or cakes.
One thing you should know about me is that I can cook, do laundry, help with homework. I also speak Spanish and Italian, which mean they could be learning a new language if wanted.
My skills include planning, multitasking, proactive, creativity, singing, and a good listen

description.originalText: She took care of my daughter for about 1 year, used to pick her up from school and prepare a snack before dinner, laundry and cooking sometimes. She was caring, fun, and easy to deal with. My daughter ended up learning a few Spanish words. Would def hire again if needed

bio.experienceSummary:
I'm passionate about fostering children's growth and development. With four years of experience, I'm patient, calm, friendly, and assertive. I communicate with parents according to their preferences and am very comfortable enforcing household rules. I enjoy many games with children, including outdoor sports, board games, and educational games.

I have some graduate school under my belt. I am CPR-trained and willing to help with cooking, meal preparation, carpooling, light housekeeping, travel, and swimming supervision. As a caregiver, I am committed to making a positive impact on children's lives and supporting families.

I'm comfortable caring for children of all ages. I hope to be a reliable childcare option for you and your family.

Hello lovely families of NYC, my name is Nica! :)

I am a professional Childcare Provider of 11 years and a newly certified Birthday Doula! I am native to Arizona, where I was raised helping in my mother's home daycare facility. I have been immersed in this work since I was a child myself and find a tremendous calling in the nurturing and developement of babies, children and youth alike. I have been doing childcare work in NYC since my move here in 2018. 

I take a Play Based approach in my work with children and deeply love incorporating art making, nature and the outdoors. I am well versed in all ages from infants to teens as well as families with multiple children. I take pride in having outstanding relationships with all my previous families. I am most notable for being extremely present and engaged. As well as flexible and reliable - because I understand every family has their unique needs! And I will do my absolute best to accommodate and support you!

With six years of experience as a babysitter, nanny, and doula, I've had the joy of helping little ones learn, grow, and let's be honest-keep me on my toes! I'm all about creating a nurturing, playful, & supportive environment where kids can thrive. Whether you need night care, date nights, a nanny share, or a travel companion for your little adventurers, I'm here for it! Kids truly make the world go round, and I love learning from them just as much as they learn from us. Looking forward to connecting and making some magic happen for your family!

description.originalText:
Kristina is a wonderful sitter and we consistently appreciate having her look after our two children (4months and 3yrs old). She is very experienced, flexible, and engaging.
She joins in singing with our older daughter who often sings song she had picked up in her Spanish class in daycare. It’s heartwarming to see Kristina simultaneously nurturing our younger baby while creating a fun and culturally enriching environment for our older daughter. And she has a great sense of humor too!

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello, my name is Brianne and I have 10+ years of previous experience nannying and babysitting children ages ranging 4 months - 14 years old. 

In May of 2019 I graduated from Washington State University and moved out to Boston and made the move to NYC three years ago. I love spending time with children and would love to spend as much time as possible with and around them in my free time. I am a great cook (can handle meal prep), can do laundry, like to organize, and love outdoor time. I enjoy arts and crafts, making puzzles, going to the park, and going for walks.

I currently have a full time job where I work M-F 9-5 p.m.  as a Transmission Engineer for a renewable developer. I am only looking work after the hours mentioned and can help on the weekends and for date nights as well. I look forward to hearing from you!

description.originalText: I hired Brianne to help me organize, sort and move family belongings for a big move. Brianne was on time, took initiative, worked well with the other people on the job and independently. I'm very happy that Brianne was part of my organizing and moving team!

bio.experienceSummary: Hello beautiful families! My name is Tia, I'm a 34-year-old career nanny with more than 10 years experience in private, in-home childcare. I specialize in infant and toddler care, where I have the most experience and experience the most joy in my work! I am passionate about the safety, education and emotional wellness of young children, which I learned at a very young age. I am the eldest of 6 children, which has directly equipped me with the heart of a natural protector and gentle caregiver. I am CPR/First Aid/AED certified, organized and extremely detail oriented. I am the Nanny that can keep up with your children's schedule, or find a full day of things to do for last minute sitting. I'd be the perfect Nanny for any home! I have a clean background and driving record, and would love to assist you with your little one(s)! I also have a strong resume with EXCELLENT references! Let's connect! I am ready to start immediately! Looking forward!

description.displayText: Tia has a GIFT!! She was able to juggle my newborn with my 3 year old so I could rest and catch up on work. If we weren't moving, I would definitely hire her full time. Thanks for everything and best of luck!!
